On Sun, May 25, 2003 at 01:35:08PM -0700, D&C Tuinstra wrote:
> I went down and manually opened the points while the distributor is in the car
> = spark.  I had my wife turn it over and = no spark....  I just tried it
> again, if I open the points with a screwdriver = spark.
> 
> what do you think?  I am at a loss.  Sorry to be a pest on the list, but I
> need some help, this one has me stumped.

Have you verified that the points are actually opening & closing while
the engine is turning over? It could be the distributor isn't seated
all the way in the groove. There is also the possibility that rubbing
block has broken off of the points. I'd verify these things as well.

